  "text": "ArangoDB implements a comprehensive authentication and authorization infrastructure with the following key components:\n\n**Authentication Infrastructure:**\n\n1. **User Management (arangod/Auth/)**: The UserManager interface (UserManager.h) is the sole point of access for users and permissions stored in `_system/_users`. UserManagerImpl.cpp provides the implementation with a local cache to avoid unnecessary disk access. The User class (User.h/cpp) manages individual user credentials and includes password verification methods.\n\n2. **JWT Token Validation (arangod/Auth/TokenCache)**: The TokenCache class implements JWT token validation and caching. It validates both HMAC-256 and ES256 JWT signatures through methods like validateJwtHMAC256Signature() and validateJwtES256Signature(). The checkAuthenticationJWT() method handles JWT parsing and validation, checking the header, body, and signature components. TokenCache::Entry stores authenticated user information including username, roles, and JWT token string.\n\n3. **HTTP Request Authentication (arangod/GeneralServer/)**: The CommTask class in CommTask.h/cpp implements the checkAuthHeader() method that extracts and validates authentication headers from incoming HTTP requests. This method is called by HttpCommTask.cpp (line 601) and H2CommTask.cpp for HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 connections respectively. The method delegates to TokenCache for JWT or Basic auth validation.\n\n4. **Authentication Configuration (arangod/GeneralServer/)**: The AuthenticationFeature class manages the authentication subsystem, including loading JWT secrets from files or folders (loadJwtSecretKeyfile(), loadJwtSecretFolder()). AuthenticationOptions.h defines configuration parameters including:\n   - authenticationUnixSockets (default: true)\n   - authenticationSystemOnly (default: true) \n   - sessionTimeout (default: 3600 seconds)\n   - minimalJwtExpiryTime and maximalJwtExpiryTime for JWT token expiry validation\n   - JWT secret configuration options (jwtSecretProgramOption, jwtSecretKeyfile, jwtSecretFolder)\n\n**Authorization Infrastructure:**\n\n5. **ExecContext (arangod/Utils/ExecContext.h/cpp)**: The ExecContext class represents the authorization context for an executing operation. It carries:\n   - Current user and database information\n   - Authentication levels (RO/RW) for system and current database\n   - JWT token and roles from JWT authentication\n   - Methods to check permissions: canUseDatabase(), canUseCollection(), collectionAuthLevel()\n   - Support for superuser context via ExecContextSuperuserScope\n   - Thread-local storage of current execution context via CURRENT static variable\n\n**REST API Endpoints:**\n\n6. **User Management Endpoint (arangod/RestHandler/RestUsersHandler)**: Implements the /_api/user REST endpoint for managing users through GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, and DELETE operations.\n\n7. **Authentication Endpoint (arangod/RestHandler/RestAuthHandler)**: Implements the /_api/auth endpoint that generates JWT tokens via generateJwt() method, accepting username and expiry parameters.\n\n8. **Access Token Management (arangod/RestHandler/RestAccessTokenHandler)**: Implements access token operations including createAccessToken(), deleteAccessToken(), and showAccessTokens() for user access token management.\n\n9. **Authentication Reload (arangod/RestHandler/RestAuthReloadHandler)**: Handles reloading of authentication configuration.\n\n**Authentication Flow:**\n1. HTTP request arrives at CommTask::checkAuthHeader()\n2. Authentication header (Bearer token or Basic auth) is extracted\n3. TokenCache::checkAuthentication() validates the token\n4. For JWT: TokenCache::checkAuthenticationJWT() parses and validates signature\n5. UserManager::checkCredentials() verifies user exists and is active\n6. ExecContext is created with user, database, and auth levels\n7. RequestHandler methods (canUseCollection, canUseDatabase) enforce authorization\n\n**Key Classes and Methods:**\n- UserManager::checkCredentials() - Main credential verification entry point\n- TokenCache::validateJwtHMAC256Signature() - JWT signature validation with HMAC\n- TokenCache::validateJwtES256Signature() - JWT signature validation with ES256\n- ExecContext::canUseCollection() - Collection-level permission check\n- ExecContext::canUseDatabase() - Database-level permission check\n- AuthenticationFeature::jwtSecrets() - Retrieves active and passive JWT secrets\n- RestUsersHandler, RestAuthHandler, RestAccessTokenHandler - REST API endpoints for user management\n"
}

